{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5c6c0cf0-ae8e-4361-bf8b-5ef28485f581","content":"Here's what breaks in each snippet when moving to .NET 10:\n\n---\n\n### Form1.cs — `ContextMenu`/`MenuItem` removed\n\nThese legacy types (obsolete-as-error since .NET 7) were **removed** in .NET 10. Replace with:\n\n```csharp\nvar menu = new ContextMenuStrip();\nmenu.Items.Add(new ToolStripMenuItem(\"Open\", image: null, OnOpen));\n```\n\nNote: the event handler signature changes from `EventHandler` to `EventHandler` (same), but the sender is now `ToolStripMenuItem`.\n\n---\n\n### ImageProcessor.cs — Exception type changed\n\n.NET 10 no longer throws `OutOfMemoryException` for invalid/corrupt image files. GDI+ error mapping was fixed — it now throws `ArgumentException`. Your `catch (OutOfMemoryException)` **will miss invalid-format errors silently**. Fix:\n\n```csharp\ncatch (ArgumentException ex)\n{\n    logger.LogError(ex, \"Invalid image format\");\n}\n```\n\nIf you also want to guard against actual OOM, catch both:\n\n```csharp\ncatch (Exception ex) when (ex is ArgumentException or OutOfMemoryException)\n```\n\n---\n\n### MainWindow.xaml — Two issues\n\n1. **Empty `<Grid.ColumnDefinitions/>` and `<Grid.RowDefinitions/>`** — Self-closing empty collection elements now produce **XAML compiler warnings** in .NET 10. Remove them if unused, or add actual definitions.\n\n2. **`{DynamicResource MissingKey}`** — .NET 10 WPF emits a **runtime diagnostic/warning** for unresolved dynamic resource keys (previously silent). Ensure `MissingKey` is defined in a resource dictionary, or remove the binding.\n\n---\n\n### Additional items you mentioned\n\n| Area | .NET 10 change | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| **StatusStrip rendering** | Default `RenderMode` changed; visual appearance differs | Set `RenderMode = ToolStripRenderMode.System` explicitly |\n| **TreeView checkboxes** | `AfterCheck` event fires more consistently (no more double-fire on click) | Review any workarounds you have fo